pr_review_comment_body:
@codiebeulaine let's add the exciting text as a default value here, like this 
{% trans "Submit Survey" as text %}
`{{self.submit_text|default:text }}`

I still don't completely understand why this test (and also many below) could not be run on Travis without credentials. If `tweepy.Cursor` is mocked and we provide sufficient data in cache then `TwitterAPI.search` method should return the desired data and test should work. Missing credentials shouldn't be a problem since we are not accessing Twitter anyway.

I haven't tested with Travis but locally, without credentials, only 2 out of 7 tests fail and even those two could probably be fixed. Even if not, we should probably run the remaining 5 on Travis.

@s-alexey if you still think we shouldn't run this on Travis, can you try to explain again why not?

there is a way simpler way of intersecting two dicts:

```python
>>> x = {1:2, 3:4}
>>> y = {1:2, 5:6}
>>> dict(x.items() & y.items())
{1: 2}
```

Do you mean something like this?

```
'st-link': {
    'uvproj' : {
        'TargetDlls': {
            'Driver': 'STLink\\ST-LINKIII-KEIL_SWO.dll',
        },
        'Utilities': {
            'Flash2': 'STLink\\ST-LINKIII-KEIL_SWO.dll',
        },
    }
    'uvopt' : {   (or maybe better 'uvoptx' because it is used only for Keil uvoptx files)
        'DebugOpt' : {
            'nTsel' : '11',
            'pMon': 'STLink\\ST-LINKIII-KEIL_SWO.dll',
        },
        'SetRegEntry' : {
            'Key' : 'ST-LINKIII-KEIL_SWO',
        },
    },
}
```

```
uvoptx_dic['ProjectOpt']['Target']['TargetOption']['DebugOpt']['nTsel'] = self.definitions.debuggers[debugger_name]['uvopt']['DebugOpt']['nTsel']
uvoptx_dic['ProjectOpt']['Target']['TargetOption']['DebugOpt']['pMon'] = self.definitions.debuggers[debugger_name]['uvopt']['DebugOpt']['pMon']
uvoptx_dic['ProjectOpt']['Target']['TargetOption']['TargetDriverDllRegistry']['SetRegEntry']['Key'] = self.definitions.debuggers[debugger_name]['uvopt']['SetRegEntry']['Key']
```
